MyPaal
In reply to this message
In Python, None is used to represent a null value or no value at all. It is not the same as 0, False, or an empty string. None is often utilized to denote the absence of a specific value or to initialize variables without assigning any values yet. It serves as a powerful tool in the Python programming language. If a variable is not assigned any value explicitly, it automatically defaults to None. It is crucial for marking missing values and handling cases where no value is expected.

MyPaal

The Mechanist, also known as Isabel Cruz, is a fictional character and robotics expert in the Commonwealth in 2287. She is the central antagonist in the Fallout 4 add-on Automatron. The character is depicted as a highly skilled engineer with intentions to help others, making the decision to kill or spare her a significant choice in the game. If spared, she remains at her lair but does not function as a settler and cannot be relocated. Killing her grants unique rewards like the Protectron's Gaze, a laser pistol. The Mechanist is a complex character with both heroic and villainous elements, embodying a blend of expertise and conflicting motivations within the Fallout universe.ü§ñ

For more details, you can visit the Fallout Fandom page.

Orbital Elements
This video shows the 6 Orbital or Keplerian Elements. These elements are used to describe the position of a body in space. Each element is shown increasing in turn, using the example of a satellite orbiting the Earth. The modelling was performed at and funded by the Aerospace Engineering Department of the University of Bristol, UK.
